			<div class="postrow has_after_content">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Ingress - Thoughts
				</h2>
				

						
						
							
						
				<div class="content ">
					<div id="post_message_1769158">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							The PVP idea would mean that each game client would also have to show the location of each player. While I don't think people would have a problem with this when actively playing the game, it's pretty easy to spot another ingress player if you're playing too, it's that it could then be used to find a person's home.<br />
<br />
Even if both players would have to be inside a certain range to see one another it might be possible to spy on others through GPS spoofing (though that's getting hard to do from what I hear) or just a plain old fashion following. A player needs to leave the app running to collect XT, which is then used to perform actions and recharge resonators on portals.<br />
<br />
I'm also afraid that ingress would go from a friendly game of capture the flag to a much more competitive and less fun. Lower level players already have issues leveling if their chosen faction controls a majority of the portals or if the other faction has too many high level portals up. With any kind of PvP interaction, high level players could just constantly attack low level players to prevent them from doing anything. One solution is to keep high level players from attacking low level players but then you just run into a Fansy the Bard situation.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="after_content">
				
                                       
                                 
				
